refsect1.para:
  Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.


    &opt_h;
    &opt_help;



        display help message and terminate





    &opt_version;



        display version information and terminate





    &opt_q;
    &opt_quiet;



        do not display warning messages





    &opt_v;
    &opt_verbose;



        display concise intermediate messages





    &opt_f;
    &opt_formats;



       list accepted formats





    &opt_i;
    &opt_in1;=&format;


use &format; format as the format for &infile1; (or &stdin; if
      &infile1; is not supplied)





    &opt_j;
    &opt_in2;=&format;


use &format; format as the format for &infile2;




    &opt_s;
    &opt_strong;


use strong bisimulation as equivalence





    &opt_b;
    &opt_branching;


use branching bisimulation as equivalence





    &opt_tau;=&actnames;


consider actions with a name in the comma separated list &actnames;
      to be a internal (tau) actions in addition to those defined as such by
      the input. This means that before comparing the LTSs all specified
      actions are first replaced by tau actions.
